        <abstract> 
<p>WTT-D’s suggestion about absorbent function of pegs in <hi rend="italic">Abronia</hi> suggests origin of pegs in <hi rend="italic">Welwitschia</hi>, which deeply interests CD. Previously could not see how pegs became large enough to be of mechanical use. Now thinks tissue between hypocotyl and radicle absorbs fluid, which would favour rise of peg to expose larger surface.</p> 
            <p>Rejects German contempt for investigating use of organs.</p> 
<p>Asks WTT-D to observe how worms draw <hi rend="italic">Robinia</hi> leaves into burrows.</p> 
        </abstract>
